⏺ That is exactly what the current file does — let me walk through it so you can
   verify:

  - Dropdowns are never narrowed. refreshCompanyLists (lines 45–60) always loads
   fetchEmployeesForCompany and fetchProjectsForCompany — the full company
  lists. Nothing else ever overwrites those employees / projects refs. So you
  can always pick any employee and any project on the company.
  - When you change employee (lines 77–91): if a project is also already
  selected, it fetches the projects allowed for that employee and only clears
  project_id when it's not in that allowed list. Valid pair → nothing happens.
  No project selected yet → early return, nothing happens.
  - When you change project (lines 93–107): symmetric — only clears employee_id
  if the currently selected employee isn't in the allowed list for that project.
   Valid pair → nothing happens.

  So the rule is: clear the other side only on mismatch, never on a valid pair,
  and the dropdowns themselves stay full. If you're seeing something different
  in the browser, can you tell me the exact steps (which company, which order
  you picked, what cleared)? That'd help me find the bug.

